6 BEST DOG BREEDS FOR KIDS

Dogs are the most wanted pet in this era. They are well-known for their responsibility and loyalty. Moreover, a pet gets attached to people when it is taken care. A pet dog who is friendly can be a good playmate for children too. They are the best playmates anyone could ask for. There is a great variation in temperament of different dogs. So, before people adopt any puppy, they prefer to search some good dog breeds for their kids. And you are reading this article for the same reason, right?

Why should we get a dog?

The people after spending a hectic day in their offices. They want to relax for some time and find someone who is available for them right after working hours. In this busy era, when all the members of family work for 16-18 hours straight, people hardly get time for their kids and other family members. A pet in the house can be a source of solace. A playful dog is the best pet for children and people in a house. All you need is to find a good dog breed.

WHAT ARE THE PROS OF OWING A DOG?

Dogs prove to be a good playmate. Owing a dog can reduce stress levels so they prove good for your mental health. If you live alone, dogs are a good company to keep and they are loyal. They can provide you security. They have a higher life expectancy unlike any other pet. Dogs can help handicapped persons. You can take them to jogging with yourself.

There are some good suggestions for you to get a best dog breed for your kids according to American Kennel Club. Surely, you will choose the one according to your lifestyle, schedule, and budget.

1. GOLDEN RETRIEVERS

These dogs are intelligent and easy to train. They are American-favorite pet. Their friendly nature gives people opportunity to get relaxed after a tiresome work day. They know how to play and are quick learners that require lots of physical activity like running, swimming and fetching a ball. You can have joyful time with them for sure.

Photo by Jayden Burdick from Pexels

2.    PUGS:

As humans are tired of this fast-racing world and want to get into the couch for a day and read a novel or watch a new movie instead of spending 16 hours work day. Pugs have some similarities with human beings. They like eating and sleeping. They live in a moderate environment. They do not survive in too hot or too cold environments. Taking care of these dogs should be your routine as they are sensitive to table scraps. You should have a good know how about their diet too. (Dur et al.)


Photo by Sebastian Coman Travel from Pexels

3. PAPILLION:

These belong to the cutest dog breeds. They have wing shaped ears that give this breed the name (Papillion is French for butterfly). These dainty dogs take to training eagerly. These are good- natured and high spirited. They love to have companionship. These are people pleaser dogs. They thrive in all seasons whether hot or cold. They love playing sports with kids. Thats why they are eager to join family gatherings.


Photo by Blue Bird from Pexels

4.CAVALIER KING CHARLES SPANIEL:

Their silky soft fur is eye catcher. Theyre so lively and good at making friends. Cavaliers get along with kids and other dogs too. Their heart- melting expression is the thing you cant ignore. The cavaliers all-around beauty, regal race, their unique face expressions, and even temper mark him as one of dogdoms noblemen. Cavaliers may be aristocrats, but they descend from their royal horse to catch a squirrel.


Photo by Steshka Willems from Pexels

5.ALASKAN MALAMUTE:

These are strong, heavy-duty worker. Alaskan are affectionate and playful dogs. In their form you can find two qualities in one dog. Theyre active and dignified dogs. Alaskan are recognized by their well-furred plumed tail carried over their back. They wag their tail when being joyful. Their almond brown colored eyes have an affectionate sparkle. Firm, but early training should be given to them in puppyhood. Everything about malamutes suggest that they belong to the arctic sled dog's origin. Their strong bones, powerful shoulders and dense bony skeleton screams that, they work hard for a living.

 


Photo by Georgios Kournoutis from Pexels

6. BEAGLE:

These are cute, friendly and absolutely lovable. They thrive on companionship and long days of loneliness doesnt work for them. Beagles are well-known for their hunting habits. They have phenomenal sense of smell too. Beagles are often used as bedbug detectors. You can find 10 fun facts about beagle on akc website. (Jun 08 et al.)

Photo by Artem Beliaikin from Pexels

WHY HAVING A DOG IS A BAD IDEA?

There are some disadvantages for having a canine companion. They require lots of training which is time consuming. They need plenty of exercise. If they are not well trained it becomes hard to deal with them and dealing with their poops is so unpleasant. Dogs come with odors, fleas, hair and chew marks which are all undesirable. They can create a lot of mess if not properly trained. Having a dog cost much. They require regular checkups and medication. Their food is expensive and in some developing countries like Pakistan you may not find desired food for them.

CONCLUSION:

What to consider before purchasing a dog? Before purchasing a dog an appropriate amount of research should be done about their good breeds, likes and dislikes. Searching about their food and availability in the market should be done. How to train them well? This research should be done. If you are capable of taking care of a pet then a dog will be a perfect choice. Just bring a good dog breed and you will have a good company to enjoy.
